title: Artie Shaw Talks 1984 - an excerpt
description: Artie Shaw was so gracious to grant me this interview. I was 26, and had no business trying to parry ideas with him, but he invited  and encouraged it. Later on, we collaborated on a few projects, and he became to me, as he was to many , a mentor. He would suggest authors to read that were to him, essential, among them Lafcadio Hearn, for which I'm forever grateful. Bravo and thank you, Mr. Shaw!
